# TempHist Cache Update Cron Jobs

# Run these commands to set up automatic cache updates

# Environment variables (add these to your crontab)

API_BASE=https://api.temphist.com
OUTPUT_DIR=/path/to/your/webroot/data
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_PATH=/path/to/your/firebase-service-account.json

# Update locations every 6 hours

0 _/6 _ \* \* cd /path/to/your/project && node scripts/fetch-locations.js >> /var/log/temphist-locations.log 2>&1

# Update temperature data (daily, weekly, monthly, yearly) every day at 3 AM

0 3 \* \* \* cd /path/to/your/project && node scripts/fetch-daily-data.js >> /var/log/temphist-temperature.log 2>&1

# Or run both together every 6 hours (recommended)

0 _/6 _ \* \* cd /path/to/your/project && node scripts/update-cache.js >> /var/log/temphist-cache.log 2>&1

# Notes:

# - Replace /path/to/your/project with your actual project path

# - Replace /path/to/your/webroot/data with your actual data directory path

# - Replace /path/to/your/firebase-service-account.json with your Firebase service account path

# - Log files will be created automatically

# - Check logs if scripts fail: tail -f /var/log/temphist-\*.log

# - The temperature data script requires Firebase authentication for production API access
